        </div>

        <!-- VENDORS -->
        <div class="row">
            
            <div class="col-xs-3 col-sm-3 col-md-2 col-lg-2 text-right-not-xs"><h4>Vendor(s)</h4></div>
            <div class="col-xs-9 col-sm-9 col-md-10 col-lg-10 adv_data">
                
                    PHOENIX CONTACT<br>
                </div>
            
        </div>

        <!-- PRODUCTS -->
        <div class="row">
            
            <div class="col-xs-3 col-sm-3 col-md-2 col-lg-2 text-right-not-xs"><h4>Product(s)</h4></div>
            <div class="col-xs-9 col-sm-9 col-md-10 col-lg-10 advisory-prod-table mt-3"><table border="1">
<tbody>
<tr>
<td><strong>Product number</strong></td>
<td><strong>Product name</strong></td>
<td><strong>Firmware version</strong></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>2313452</td>
<td>FL COMSERVER UNI 232/422/485</td>
<td>&lt; 2.40</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>2904817</td>
<td>FL COMSERVER UNI 232/422/485-T</td>
<td>&lt; 2.40</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table></div>
            
        </div>

        <!-- Advisory Summary -->
        <!-- SUMMARY -->
        
        <div class="row">
            
            <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-3 col-md-2 col-lg-2 text-right-not-xs"><h4>Summary</h4></div>
            <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-9 col-md-10 col-lg-10 adv_data" style="margin-top: 10px; display: block;"><p>When the communication partner sends an invalid Modbus exception response to the FL COMSERVER UNI as a query, the Modbus communication stops, and the device will be unresponsive for some minutes before the functionality is fully restored (CWE-772).</p>
<div></div></div>
            
        </div>
        

        <hr class="adv-dt-cve-hr">

        
            <!-- CVE ID -->
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-xs-3 col-sm-3 col-md-2 col-lg-2 text-right-not-xs"><h4>CVE ID</h4></div>
                <div class="col-xs-9 col-sm-9 col-md-10 col-lg-10 adv_data">
                
                    <a href="https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2021-21002" target="_blank">
                    CVE-2021-21002&nbsp;</a></div>
                
            </div>

            <!-- SEVERITY -->
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-xs-3 col-sm-3 col-md-2 col-lg-2 text-right-not-xs"><h4>Severity</h4></div>
                <div class="col-xs-9 col-sm-9 col-md-10 col-lg-10 ellipsis-1 adv_data">
                    
                        
                            <span class="label label-md label-warning label-cve">7.5</span>
                        
                    
                    
                        <!-- https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln-metrics/cvss/v3-calculator?vector=AV:N/AC:L/PR:H/UI:N/S:C/C:H/I:H/A:H&version=3.1 -->
                        <a href="https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln-metrics/cvss/v3-calculator?vector=AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:N/A:H&version=3.1" target="_blank">
                        (CVSS:3.1:AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:N/A:H)&nbsp;</a>
                    
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- VULN_TYPE -->
            <div class="row">                <!-- https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/476.html -->
                <div class="col-xs-3 col-sm-3 col-md-2 col-lg-2 text-right-not-xs"><h4>Weakness</h4></div>
                <div class="col-xs-9 col-sm-9 col-md-10 col-lg-10 adv_data">Missing Release of Resource after Effective Lifetime&nbsp;<a href="https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/-772
.html" target="_blank">
                     (
CWE-772
)&nbsp;</a></div>
            </div>

            <!-- SUMMARY -->
            
                <div class="row">
                    <div class="col-xs-3 col-sm-3 col-md-2 col-lg-2 text-right-not-xs"><h4>Summary</h4></div>
                    <div class="col-xs-9 col-sm-9 col-md-10 col-lg-10 adv_data" style="margin-top: 10px;">In Phoenix Contact FL COMSERVER UNI in versions < 2.40 a invalid Modbus exception response can lead to a temporary denial of service.</div>
                </div>
            

            <!-- SOURCE -->
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-xs-3 col-sm-3 col-md-2 col-lg-2 text-right-not-xs"><h4>Source</h4></div>
                <div class="col-xs-9 col-sm-9 col-md-10 col-lg-10 adv_data">
                    
                        <a href="https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2021-21002" target="_blank">
                    
                    nvd.nist.gov&nbsp;</a>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- IMPACT -->
            


            <!-- SOLUTION -->
            

            <!-- REPORTED_BY -->
            
        
        <hr style="border-top: 1px solid #c8d2eb; width: 80%;">

        <!-- Advisory Summary, Impact and Solution -->

        <!-- IMPACT -->
        
        <div class="row">
            
            <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-3 col-md-2 col-lg-2 text-right-not-xs"><h4>Impact</h4></div>
            <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-9 col-md-10 col-lg-10" style="margin-top: 10px;"><p>An attacker may use this vulnerability to execute a Denial of Service (DoS) attack.</p>
<div></div></div>
            
        </div>
        

        <!-- SOLUTION -->
        
        <div class="row">
            
            <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-3 col-md-2 col-lg-2 text-right-not-xs"><h4>Solution</h4></div>
            <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-9 col-md-10 col-lg-10 advisory_detail" style="margin-top: 10px;"><p>PHOENIX CONTACT recommends affected users to upgrade to the latest firmware version which is available for download.</p>
<table border="1">
<tbody>
